# ArysAI Cline Rules

## Project structure
- Worker code: worker/ (Cloudflare Worker, ES modules, no bundler)
- Production frontend: docs/ (GitHub Pages, ES module imports, no bundler)
- Minimal frontend: frontend/ (standalone, no framework, no bundler)

## Coding standards
- ES module syntax everywhere (import/export) — no require()
- Never commit API keys — use `wrangler secret put` for secrets
- All worker responses must include CORS headers from getCorsHeaders()
- Worker SSE events must use the schema in worker/utils.js:
    {type: "text", content: "..."} | {type: "search", status: {...}}
    | {type: "done"} | {type: "error", error: "..."}
- docs/js/utils.js must only export pure utility functions — never re-export
  from other modules (config, api, markdown) to avoid circular imports

## Dependencies
- No browser automation libs (puppeteer, selenium) in production deps
- Worker has no npm dependencies at runtime — Cloudflare Workers API only

## Deployment
- Worker: `npm run deploy` (wrangler deploy)
- Frontend: push to main → GitHub Actions publishes docs/ to Pages
- Bump version in docs/js/config.js and worker file headers on each release

## Testing
- Worker locally: `wrangler dev`
- Frontend locally: `npx serve docs` (port 8788 to match wrangler proxy)